 into it and season with salt and pepper. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>12-15 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b> or until chicken is cooked through. Remove Varoma and transfer chicken into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl. Cover to keep warm and set aside."},{"content":"Blend leek mixture <b>1 min\/speed 4<b> <strong>-9, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 9<\/strong>. Transfer into bowl with parsley, then cover and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place oil, onion, garlic, lemon zest and lemon thyme into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Drain mushrooms. Add soaked mushrooms, fresh mushrooms, reserved leek mixture, salt and pepper and cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Add mushroom sauce to thermal serving bowl and stir well with aid of spatula. Divide zucchini between serving bowls and top with creamy mushroom and chicken mixture. Garnish with extra lemon thyme before serving."}],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","6 portions"]}